1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-7\" href=\"https:\/\/applyjobs.org.ng\/how-to-become-a-neurosurgeon-in-canada\/#Top_Global_Universities_for_Neuroscience_and_Behavior_in_Canada\" title=\"Top Global Universities for Neuroscience and Behavior in Canada\">Top Global Universities for Neuroscience and Behavior in Canada<\/a><\/li><\/ul><\/nav><\/div>\n\n<p style=\"padding-left: 40px; text-align: center;\">\u00a0<strong>Education to be become a Neurosurgeon is rigorous and extensive, it demand some certain education qualification which you will get to know after reading this content.<\/strong><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"size-medium wp-image-2255 aligncenter\" src=\"https:\/\/www.applyjobs.org.ng\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/09\/spinalcordnerves-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"How to Become a Neurosurgeon in Canada\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" title=\"\"><\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p><strong>Contents<\/strong><\/p>\n<p><a href=\"#_Toc83065419\">Definition<\/a><\/p>\n<p><a href=\"#_Toc83065420\">Duration of years to become a Neurosurgeon<\/a><\/p>\n<p><a href=\"#_Toc83065421\">Estimated salaries<\/a><\/p>\n<p><a href=\"#_Toc83065422\">Most common operation carried out by Neurosurgeons<\/a><\/p>\n<p><a href=\"#_Toc83065423\">Education Qualification<\/a><\/p>\n<p><a href=\"#_Toc83065425\">High School Required Subject<\/a><\/p>\n<p><a href=\"#_Toc83065426\">Top Global Universities for Neuroscience and Behavior in Canada<\/a><\/p>\n<h2 id=\"definition-how-to-become-a-neurosurgeon\"><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Definition_How_to_Become_a_Neurosurgeon\"><\/span><a name=\"_Toc83065419\"><\/a>Definition| How to Become a Neurosurgeon<img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"size-medium wp-image-2257 alignright\" src=\"https:\/\/www.applyjobs.org.ng\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/09\/definition-300x169.png\" alt=\"How to Become a Neurosurgeon in Canada\" width=\"300\" height=\"169\" title=\"\"><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<p>A neurosurgeon is a physician that specializes in the diagnosis and surgical treatment of disorders of the central and peripheral nervous system including the following:<\/p>\n<ul>\n<li>Congenital anomalies<\/li>\n<li>Trauma<\/li>\n<li>Tumors<\/li>\n<li>Vascular<\/li>\n<li>Infections of the brain or spine and also<\/li>\n<li>Stroke disease of the spine.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h2 id=\"duration-of-years\"><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Duration_of_years\"><\/span><a name=\"_Toc83065420\"><\/a>Duration of years<img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"size-medium wp-image-2258 alignright\" src=\"https:\/\/www.applyjobs.org.ng\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/09\/www.usnews.com_-300x197.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"197\" title=\"\"><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<p>Education required to become a neu.surgeon is rigorous and extensive, it required less than <strong>four years in undergraduate<\/strong> studies, and <strong>four years in medical<\/strong> school <strong>and seven years in fellowship training<\/strong>.<\/p>\n<h2 id=\"estimated-neu-surgeon-salaries\"><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Estimated_Neusurgeon_salaries\"><\/span><a name=\"_Toc83065421\"><\/a>Estimated Neu.surgeon salaries<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<p>The minimum salary is $242,200 a year, with salaries ranging from $60,402 to $502,004.<\/p>\n<h2 id=\"most-common-operation-carried-out-by-neurosurgeons\"><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Most_common_operation_carried_out_by_Neurosurgeons\"><\/span><a name=\"_Toc83065422\"><\/a>Most common operation carried out by Neurosurgeons<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Craniotomy<\/li>\n<li>Chiari Decompression<\/li>\n<li>Epilepsy surgery<\/li>\n<li>Laminectomy<\/li>\n<li>Anterior Cervical Discectomy.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h2 id=\"education-qualification-how-to-become-a-neurosurgeon\"><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Education_Qualification_How_to_Become_a_Neurosurgeon\"><\/span><a name=\"_Toc83065423\"><\/a>Education Qualification<a name=\"_Toc83065424\"><\/a>| How to Become a Neurosurgeon<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Medical Degree (4-6 years)<\/li>\n<li>Internship (1 year)<\/li>\n<li>Vocational training (5years+)<\/li>\n<li>Residency (1 or more years).<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h2 id=\"high-school-required-subject-how-to-become-a-neurosurgeon\"><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"High_School_Required_Subject_How_to_Become_a_Neurosurgeon\"><\/span><a name=\"_Toc83065425\"><\/a>High School Required Subject| How to Become a Neurosurgeon<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Organic chemistry<\/li>\n<li>Biology<\/li>\n<li>Chemistry<\/li>\n<li>Physics<\/li>\n<li>English Language<\/li>\n<li>Advanced mathematics including statistics.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h2 id=\"top-global-universities-for-neuroscience-and-behavior-in-canada\"><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Top_Global_Universities_for_Neuroscience_and_Behavior_in_Canada\"><\/span><a name=\"_Toc83065426\"><\/a>Top Global Universities for Neuroscience and Behavior in Canada<img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"size-medium wp-image-2254 alignright\" src=\"https:\/\/www.applyjobs.org.ng\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/09\/neoro-300x164.jpg\" alt=\"How to Become a Neurosurgeon in Canada\" width=\"300\" height=\"164\" title=\"\"><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<ul>\n<li>University of Toronto<\/li>\n<li>McGill University<\/li>\n<li>University of the British Columbia<\/li>\n<li>Calgary University<\/li>\n<li>University of Montreal<\/li>\n<li>Western University<\/li>\n<li>McMaster University<\/li>\n<li>The University of Ottawa.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><strong>see also &gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;<\/strong><a title=\"How to Become a Med Lab-scientist\" href=\"https:\/\/www.applyjobs.org.ng\/how-to-become-a-med-lab-scientist\/\" rel=\"bookmark nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>How to Become a Med Lab-scientist<\/strong><\/a><\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"How to Become a Neurosurgeon in Canada-, Duration of Study, Education qualification, Graduate Entrance, High School Required Subjects.&hellip;\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":2253,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"footnotes":""},"categories":[14],"tags":[728],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/applyjobs.org.ng\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/2252"}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/applyjobs.org.ng\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/applyjobs.org.ng\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/applyjobs.org.ng\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/1"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/applyjobs.org.ng\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=2252"}],"version-history":[{"count":1,"href":"https:\/\/applyjobs.org.ng\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/2252\/revisions"}],"predecessor-version":[{"id":19059,"href":"https:\/\/applyjobs.org.ng\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/2252\/revisions\/19059"}],"wp:featuredmedia":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/applyjobs.org.ng\/wp-json\/"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/applyjobs.org.ng\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media?parent=2252"}],"wp:term":[{"taxonomy":"category","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/applyjobs.org.ng\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/categories?post=2252"},{"taxonomy":"post_tag","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/applyjobs.org.ng\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/tags?post=2252"}],"curies":[{"name":"wp","href":"https:\/\/api.w.org\/{rel}","templated":true}]}}